APR 10 1990

suBject: Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon 

Constitution Amendment No. XIII

to: Deputy to Assistant Secretary - Indian Affairs (Tribal Services 

Division of Tribal Government Services Attn: Pat Simmons MAILSTOP 
4627 MIB

Attached for information is the approval of the Confederated Tribes of 

the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon Constitution Amendment No. XIII 

dated March 27, 1990. Attached with it are the Certificate of Results of 

Election, Approval by Portland Area Director, Amendment A, and' the 

Official Ballot. Amendment A is now renumbered Amendment XIII, Article 

V, Section I .

Attachment

MAR 27 1990

attnof: Portland Area Director

subject: Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon 

Constitution Amendment No. XIII

TO: Superintendent, Warm Springs Agency

On March 6, 1990, the Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation 
of Oregon voted on one (1) proposed amendment (Amendment A) to the tribal 
constitution and bylaws.

As recommended by the Superintendent's transmitted of the Certificate of 
Results of Election, Amendment A Is renumbered as Amendment XIII, and is 
hereby approved and worded as follows:
 
 

AMENDMENT XIII

 
 ARTICLE V, Section 1

(e) To borrow money from the federal government in accordance 
with the terms of a corporate charter to be issued to the 
Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon 
and to borrow money for public purposes in accordance with terms 
to be approved by Tribal Referendum; and

The tribe and its leadership are to be commended for their efforts in 
up-dating their constitution and bylaws.

We would like a copy of the tribes' constitution and bylaws which 
incorporates their new amendment as soon as convenient.
 
  
 

AMENDMENT 
CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS 
 
 of the  
 
CONFEDERATED TRIBES OF THE WARM SPRINGS 
RESERVATION OF OREGON

AMENDMENT A


ARTICLE V, Section 1

(e) To borrow money from the federal government in accordance with the 

terms of a corporate charter to be issued to the Confederated Tribes of 

the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon and to borrow money for public 

purposes in accordance with terms to be approved by Tribal Referendum; and
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to an election authorized by the Assistant Area Director (Program 
Services) on February 8, 1990, the attached AMENDMENT to the Constitution of 
The Confederated Tribes of Warm Springs Indian Reservation, was submitted to 
the qualified voters of the tribe and on March 6, 1990, was duly adopted by a 
vote of 143 FOR, and 139 AGAINST, and 8 CAST BALLOTS found spoiled or 
mutilated," in an election in which at least 30 percent of the 550 entitled to 
vote, cast their ballots in accordance with Section 16 of the Reorganization 

Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended by the Act of June 15, 1935 
(49 Stat. 378).
 
 

APPROVAL

 
 I, Portland Area Director, Bureau of Indian Affairs, Portland, Oregon, by 

virtue of the authority granted to the Secretary of the Interior of the 

United States, by the Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended, 

and delegated to me by 10 BIAM, Section 2, Release 44, February 18, 1989, 

incorporating 230 DM Release No. 2784 dated March 16, 1988, do hereby 

approve the foregoing Amendment to the Constitution and Bylaws of the 

Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon. This 

amendment was adopted by a majority of the qualified voters of the said 

Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon voting on 

March 6, 1990.

ACTING Portland Area 

Director

Bureau of Indian Affairs

Portland, Oregon

Dated MAR 27 1990
 
  
 

