to: Superintendent, Warm Springs Agency

On March 6, 1990, the Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation 
of Oregon voted on one (I) proposed amendment (Amendment A) to the tribal 
constitution and bylaws.

As recommended by the Superintendent's transmitted of the Certificate of 
Results of Election, Amendment A, and is
hereby approved and worded as follows:
 
 

AMENDMENT XI I I

 
 ARTICLE V, Section 1

(e) To borrow money from the federal government In accordance 
with the terms of a corporate charter to be issued to the 
Confederated Tribes of the Warm Springs Reservation of Oregon 
and to borrow money for public purposes in accordance with terms 
to be approved by Tribal Referendum; and

The tribe and its leadership are to be comnended for their efforts in 
up-dating their constitution and bylaws.

We would like a copy of the tribes' constitution and bylaws which 
incorporates their new amendment as soon as convenient.
 
  
 

